-- Bankers say will work with Obama on crisis
-- 
-- Fri Mar 27, 2009 1:51pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/03/27/us-obama-bank-meeting-idUSTRE52Q53S20090327

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - President Barack Obama, meeting with top U.S. bankers on Friday, emphasized the need to work together to solve the financial crisis and lift the economy out of recession. 

 "The basic message is we're all in this together," Wells Fargo chief executive John Stumpf told reporters after the meeting. (Reporting by  Caren Bohan ; Editing by  John O'Callaghan )